<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7396> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7396" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Legatus under Brutus in 42 (Plut. Brut. 51.2, Labeo; cf. 12.3, Labeo; App. BC 4.135, Labeo). In Gellius his name is given as Pacuvius Labeo (NA 5.21.10), which Badian (Salmon Studies 152-153) and Shackleton Bailey (Studies 103) accept as the proper form of his name: his son, M. Antistius Labeo, the jurist, had been adopted by an Antistius.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6179> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6179" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "One of the conspirators against Caesar, who served as a Legate under Brutus at Philippi, and compelled his slaves to kill him after the battle (Plut. Brut. 51, cf. 12; App. BC 4.135)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10483> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10483" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/21> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Plut. Brut. 12.4-6. Participant in conspiracy to kill Caesar." .
